description: Creates an Amazon SageMaker Partner AI App.

parameters.name: Name
parameters.description: The name to give the SageMaker Partner AI App.

parameters.name: Type
parameters.description: The type of SageMaker Partner AI App to create. Must be one of the following: lakera-guard, comet, deepchecks-llm-evaluation, or fiddler.

parameters.name: ExecutionRoleArn
parameters.description: The ARN of the IAM role that the partner application uses.

parameters.name: MaintenanceConfig
parameters.description: Maintenance configuration settings for the SageMaker Partner AI App. MaintenanceWindowStart (string) --- The day and time of the week in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) 24-hour standard time that weekly maintenance updates are scheduled. This value must take the following format: 3-letter-day:24-h-hour:minute. For example: TUE:03:30.

nested_params.name: MaintenanceWindowStart
nested_params.description: The day and time of the week in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) 24-hour standard time that weekly maintenance updates are scheduled. This value must take the following format: 3-letter-day:24-h-hour:minute. For example: TUE:03:30.

parameters.name: Tier
parameters.description: Indicates the instance type and size of the cluster attached to the SageMaker Partner AI App.

parameters.name: ApplicationConfig
parameters.description: Configuration settings for the SageMaker Partner AI App. AdminUsers (list) --- The list of users that are given admin access to the SageMaker Partner AI App. (string) --- Arguments (dict) --- This is a map of required inputs for a SageMaker Partner AI App. Based on the application type, the map is populated with a key and value pair that is specific to the user and application. parameters.name: AuthType
parameters.description: The authorization type that users use to access the SageMaker Partner AI App.

parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description: A unique token that guarantees that the call to this API is idempotent. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

parameters.name: Tags
parameters.description: Each tag consists of a key and an optional value. Tag keys must be unique per resource.
